
- Obey Cache-Control headers - the library should appreciate the server knows
  what it wants and skip polling if the cache headers dicate it's polling at a
  quicker interval than is needed. 
- Obey Retry-After headers - the library should not poll before a given retry
  interval. 
- Circuit break the polling and send to sleep if something is broken.
- Make client-side friendly
- Allow users to inject superagent headers, timeout etc.
- Write a sample application.

